article.description: Ashley Barlow scored the first eight points of a 10-0 rally in the second half, leading Notre Dame to a 65-56 victory over Providence on Saturday.
article.headline: Notre Dame rides 10-0 run in second half to win
article.linkText: No. 22 Notre Dame rides rally past Providence
article.story:
PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Ashley Barlow scored the first eight points of a 10-0 rally in the second half, leading Notre Dame (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP)
 to a 65-56 victory over Providence on Saturday.

Notre Dame (20-7, 9-6 Big East) and Providence (10-18, 4-10) were tied at 41 when Barlow buried consecutive 3-pointers and then scored on a layup after her steal.

Natalie Novosel's basket capped the 10-0 run as the Irish built a 51-41 lead.

Lindsay Schrader led the Irish with 18 points and Becca Bruszewski added 16. Schrader became the 25th player in program history to score 1,000 points in a career.

Chelsea Marandola led Providence with 15 points.

Notre Dame is 17-0 all-time against Providence, including 9-0 at Alumni Hall.

The Irish, who scored 40 points in the paint, have won 20 games for the 15th time in the past 16 seasons.
